<p>This session focuses on how to design work (jobs, operational frameworks, and organizational design) in times of fast-paced change and when agility and adaptability are the keys to success.<br><br>Hear from Alisa Nagle, Managing Director @ McDermott + Bull, Cristina Juvier, Global Head of HR @ Reuters, Linda Cai, Global Head of Learning, Leadership and Talent Development @ Aon, Maria Barrera, Director of Partnerships &amp; Growth @ ChartHop, and Kerry Puglisi, Head of People and Culture, Joyboard, to learn about:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>The fundamentals of agility and the implications and applications in work design</li><li>How to redesign work in times of ability and adaptability</li><li>Successful cases of work redesign using agility</li><li>How HR leaders and practitioners can design work using the fundamentals of agile design to become more adaptable</li></ul>
